# Unique Design Style Guidelines

## 1. Establish a Unique Design Style
- **Brand Consistency**: Use the Modern & Muted color palette consistently across all screens
- **Unique Visual Elements**: Implement custom arrow tiles with subtle gradients and shadows
- **Custom Components**: Design exclusive UI components with distinctive shapes and transitions

## 2. Color Scheme Optimization
- **Color Harmony**: Use the defined palette (Misty Blue, Terracotta, Olive Green, Dusty Pink)
- **Emotional Colors**: Apply colors purposefully - blue for calm, terracotta for energy
- **High Contrast**: Maintain graphite text (#4A4A4A) on light backgrounds for readability

## 3. Typography Refinement
- **Font Choices**: Use system fonts with careful weight selection
- **Clear Hierarchy**: Implement consistent text sizing (headings: 24-32pt, body: 14-16pt)
- **Consistency**: Maintain uniform text styles across all screens

## 4. Visual Engagement
- **Icon Clarity**: Use clear, minimalist icons for navigation and actions
- **Micro-Interactions**: Implement subtle animations for tile selections, transitions, and feedback
- **Balanced Motion**: Keep animations between 200-300ms for responsiveness

## 5. Attention to Detail
- **Spacing and Alignment**: Use consistent padding (16-24px) and maintain proper alignment
- **State Feedback**: Provide clear visual feedback for all interactive elements
- **Icons and Graphics**: Use distinctive arrow designs that remain clear at all sizes

## 6. Innovative Layout
- **Grid-Based Design**: Implement an elegant grid system for game boards and menus
- **Intuitive Navigation**: Create a bottom navigation bar with clear, accessible icons
- **Responsive Design**: Ensure layouts adapt gracefully to different screen sizes